# <type>(<scope>): <subject>

# <body>

# <footer>

# Type: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
# Scope: effect, platform, cli, cluster, ai, native, etc.
# Subject: imperative mood, lowercase, no period at end
# 
# Body: Explain what and why (not how)
# 
# Footer: 
# - References: "Closes #123", "Fixes #456", "Related to #789"
# - BREAKING CHANGE: description of breaking changes
# - DCO Sign-off added automatically with -s flag
#
# Examples:
# feat(native): add new sqlite adapter package
# fix(effect): correct type inference for Schema.struct
# docs(platform): update HTTP client examples
#
# For upstream contributions:
# - Follow Effect's contribution guidelines
# - Reference upstream issues when applicable
# - Use DCO sign-off: git commit -s
#
# For fork packages (packages-native/):
# - Use "native" or specific package name as scope
# - Clearly indicate if change affects compatibility